e7yf7YMvDWKg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating FileAccessRes Class**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the FileAccessRes class and how the getResource method is likely returning null for dynamically generated temp resources. It seems I need to utilize the ClassLoader to properly load the resource. I'll also have to use the correct path in the test while ensuring I preserve the original resource. There’s a bit of complexity here, but getting this right is essential to avoid issues in the future.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JlruSNwNp49jeZHiVorXNCoq|fc_0aa9f28d5101e1480169f17b31f91c81a2a4465b7df7ec7452", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RAFileInJarTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_hsqldb.hsqldb;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.PreparedStatement;\nimport java.sql.ResultSet;\nimport java.sql.Statement;\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDataSource;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\npublic class RAFileInJarTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path tempDir;\n\n    @Test\n    public void readsCachedTableDataThroughResDatabaseResources() throws Exception {\n        String databaseName = uniqueDatabaseName();\n        Path databasePath = tempDir.resolve(databaseName);\n\n        createCachedDatabase(databasePath);\n\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new